In the mood for something sweet? Dates stuffed with nuts are an excellent gluten-free snack option. Medjool dates are plump, moist, and larger than other dates. You can use peanut butter instead of chocolate.(melted or diced) Ingredients Preparation Step 1 Using a sharp knife, slit into the dates and remove the pit. You can either stuff the whole date or spit it into two. Fill the date with a walnut half. Step 2 Mix cardamom with shredded coconut and chocolate. Step 3 Sprinkle coconut over the dates, one at a time. Press the coconut into the dates, if necessary. Coat with the melted chocolate. Freeze or enjoy with friends and family.